      • sceneExists

        public java.lang.Boolean sceneExists(java.lang.String fxml_name)
        This function returns true if a certain scene already exists, and false otherwise. It should be utilized regularly before switching scenes in order to prevent reinitializing FX's and LC's over and over. Regular utilization will lead to extreme acceleration of scene switching.
        Parameters:
        fxml_name - name
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating whether the scene already exists.
